text: Hanuš is a Czech name, which may be either a given name or a common family name. ==First names== * Hanuš Schwaiger (1854–1912), Czech artist * Hanuš Wihan (1855–1920), Czech cellist * Jan Růže, also known as Master Hanuš, a Prague blacksmith apocryphally believed to have carried out the most important modification of the Prague astronomical clock ==Family names== * Jan Hanuš (composer) (1915–2004), Czech composer * Jan Hanuš (footballer) (born 1988), Czech footballer for FK Jablonec * Josef Hanuš (astronomer) (born 1983), a Czech planetary astronomer * Josef Jan Hanuš (1911–1992), Czech fighter pilot * Lumír Ondřej Hanuš (born 1947), Czech analytic chemist ==See also== * 27986 Hanuš, an asteroid named after composer Jan Hanuš * 66151 Josefhanuš, an asteroid named after the astronomer * Hanus (disambiguation)
title: Hanuš
